CP(1)

NAME
    cp - copy a file

SYNOPSIS
    cp src dst

DESCRIPTION
    cp copies src to dst. If dst names an existing directory, cp copies src
    into that directory using the source basename.

    Existing regular files at dst are truncated and replaced.

EXAMPLES
    cp /var/log/boot.txt /tmp/boot.txt
    cp /boot/splash.bmp /tmp

SEE ALSO
    mv(1), rm(1), touch(1)
